Galactoglycerolipid Degradation 1 (PGD1) identified in Chlamydomonas catalyzes the hydrolysis of acyl chains at the sn-1 position of the glycerol backbone of the plastidial MGDG (Li et al., 2012a). Lyso-MGDG were identified in Microchlorpsis gaditana. So far, no homologous gene to PGD1 was identified in NagaB31_1.0. Even if no chloroplast transit peptide was predicted, Li et al. suggest a plastidial localization of PGD1.
